-- Taiwanese Stock Movers: CoAsia, E-Ton Solar, Wintek, Yulon Motor
-- B y   B l o o m b e r g   N e w s
-- 2012-07-04T05:50:45Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-07-04/taiwanese-stock-movers-coasia-e-ton-solar-wintek-yulon-motor.html
Shares of the following companies had
 unusual  moves in Taiwan trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of the close in Taipei.  The  Taiex Index (TWSE)  added 0.1 percent to 7,422.59, capping a
four-day, 3.5 percent gain.  CoAsia Microelectronics Corp. (8096)  (8096 TT), which provides
integrated circuit design services, tumbled 7 percent to
NT$36.05, the biggest drop since June 4. CoAsia said Samsung
Taiwan will sell memory chips directly to HTC Corp., bypassing
the company as a distributor.  E-Ton Solar Tech Co. (3452)  (3452 TT), a manufacturer of solar
cells, advanced 2.4 percent to NT$15.25. Sales rose 32 percent
from a year earlier in June, according to a statement filed to
the Taiwan Stock Exchange.  Wintek Corp. (2384)  (2384 TT), a maker of liquid crystal displays,
dropped 3.3 percent to NT$16. Consolidated sales dropped 28
percent from a year earlier to NT$7.3 billion ($244.9 million)
in June, the company said in a statement.  Yulon Motor Co. (2201)  (2201 TT), an automaker, added 1 percent to
NT$52.70. The company said itâ€™s evaluating plans to enter the
Russian market as part of an overseas expansion strategy.  To contact Bloomberg News staff for this story:
